rComments: Andie is great! She really knows how to teach concepts and make them stay in your head. Unlike other profs, if there is something important we need to know, like a certain theorem, she literally underlines and explains it again for the test. also drops hints for tests which really helped. take her class and you won't regret it
A really good prof that helps out her students, but she did make a lot of mistakes when she taught. Still amazing overall

Andie was an awesome professor for first year Calculus. Very accessible and friendly, really cared about your success. Very fair regarding tests as well - if it's clear that a TA marked a question wrong she will fix it and give you credit. It's a hard course no matter who teaches it. Lectures were alright, she drops hints for test questions
She is a pretty good teacher. Great sense of humour. How ever her style of teaching is quite interesting as she could end up under preparing you for tests
